    573          /***************************************************************************//**
    574           * @brief
    575           *   Writes data to flash memory. Write data must be aligned to words and
    576           *   contain a number of bytes that is divisible by four.
    577           * @note
    578           *   It is recommended to erase the flash page before performing a write.
    579           *
    580           *   For IAR Embedded Workbench, Simplicity Studio and GCC this will be achieved
    581           *   automatically by using attributes in the function proctype. For Keil
    582           *   uVision you must define a section called "ram_code" and place this manually
    583           *   in your project's scatter file.
    584           *
    585           *   The Flash memory is organized into 64-bit wide double-words.
    586           *   Each 64-bit double-word can be written only twice using burst write
    587           *   operation between erasing cycles. The user's application must store data in
    588           *   RAM to sustain burst write operation.
    589           *
    590           *   EFR32XG21 RevC is not able to program every word twice before the next erase.
    591           *
    592           * @param[in] address
    593           *   Pointer to the flash word to write to. Must be aligned to words.
    594           * @param[in] data
    595           *   Data to write to flash.
    596           * @param[in] numBytes
    597           *   Number of bytes to write to flash. NB: Must be divisable by four.
    598           * @return
    599           *   Returns the status of the write operation, @ref MSC_Status_TypeDef
    600           * @verbatim
    601           *   flashReturnOk - Operation completed successfully.
    602           *   flashReturnInvalidAddr - Operation tried to write to a non-flash area.
    603           *   flashReturnLocked - MSC registers are locked or the operation tried to
    604           *                       program a locked area of the flash.
    605           *   flashReturnTimeOut - Operation timed out.
    606           * @endverbatim
    607           ******************************************************************************/
