   1916           *   reading and writing the existing values in memory. I.e. all data is
   1917           *   preserved. The initialization process runs in a critical section
   1918           *   disallowing interrupts and thread scheduling, and will consume a
   1919           *   considerable amount of clock cycles. Therefore the user should carefully
   1920           *   assess where to call this function. The user can consider to increase
